name: Kayvon Beykpour
tweet: Thank you to everybody who believe in the vision and supported us along the way (including our earliest investors and advocates like @scottbelsky... and @Twitter when they acquired us). Goodbye, Periscope ‚ù§Ô∏è

name: Kayvon Beykpour
tweet: I‚Äôm also grateful that the legacy of Periscope lives on and I believe can shine even brighter than the Periscope app itself. It lives on in the team members who built it, the infrastructure that powered it and the learnings it continues to inform (üëÄ @TwitterSpaces).

name: Kayvon Beykpour
tweet: I can‚Äôt thank you all enough for the love and energy you all put into the community and for the feedback you gave us all along the way. I know many of you are disappointed that Periscope is going away, and I hope you‚Äôll understand that we did not make the decision lightly.

name: Kayvon Beykpour
tweet: I‚Äôm grateful to the community that brought Periscope alive on a daily basis. You showed us the world, you shared with us your lives, you showed us some of the most important things that happened around the globe since day 1 of the app. YOU made Periscope just as much as we did.

name: Kayvon Beykpour
tweet: I‚Äôm grateful for the team that made the Periscope dream come to life. Insanely talented, relentlessly creative, and such a privilege to work with. I‚Äôm blessed to be able to work with many of them still today, and am in awe of what so many have gone on to achieve.

name: Kayvon Beykpour
tweet: I had never worked so much and so hard in my life as those first few years of Periscope, and yet it felt nothing like ‚Äúwork‚Äù. I‚Äôm grateful because that time will always serve as a reminder that life‚Äôs too short to not work on what you love.

name: Kayvon Beykpour
tweet: Today's very bittersweet, but I‚Äôm mostly filled with gratitude. I‚Äôm grateful because the experience of building Periscope was when I first learned how it feels to pour your heart & soul into building something and to feel reciprocated with utter love and satisfaction in return.
